New Features and Important Changes in ctools 1.7.1

4 September 2020


Introduction
------------
This document briefly summarizes the changes that have been made in this
ctools release with respect to the precedent release.


Configuration
-------------
The Python include path was added in the Python.h header check in configure.ac
since due to a bug introduced in Python 3.8 the cpython/initconfig.h header was
not found (#3329).


Documentation
-------------
The units of the response cubes were added to the reference manual (#3321).


Python interface
----------------
The configuration now checks for Big Sur and later so that the path names in
the Python modules are adapted as needed (#3326).

The Python module is now copied from pyext/build/ctools/ctools into
pyext/ctools since code generated using recent swig versions needs the module
in that place (#3322).


Support model
